<ns941:section xmlns:ns941="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.atam.methodology.elicitation">

  <ns942:title xmlns:ns942="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Elicitation</ns942:title>
  <ns943:para xmlns:ns943="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     During this phase the business vision, goals, the desired quality attributes and the
     chosen architecture are communicated.
    The core steps during the elicitation phase of ATAM are
    <ns944:orderedlist xmlns:ns944="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns945:listitem xmlns:ns945="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns946:para xmlns:ns946="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Present the ATAM.</ns946:para></ns945:listitem>
      <ns947:listitem xmlns:ns947="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns948:para xmlns:ns948="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Present the business drivers.</ns948:para></ns947:listitem>
      <ns949:listitem xmlns:ns949="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns950:para xmlns:ns950="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Present the architecture.</ns950:para></ns949:listitem>
      <ns951:listitem xmlns:ns951="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns952:para xmlns:ns952="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify architectural approaches.</ns952:para></ns951:listitem>
      <ns953:listitem xmlns:ns953="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns954:para xmlns:ns954="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Generate a quality attribute utility tree.</ns954:para></ns953:listitem>
      <ns955:listitem xmlns:ns955="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns956:para xmlns:ns956="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analyze architectural approaches.</ns956:para></ns955:listitem>
    </ns944:orderedlist>
  </ns943:para>
  
  <ns957:section xmlns:ns957="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns958:title xmlns:ns958="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Present the ATAM</ns958:title>
    <ns959:para xmlns:ns959="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The ATAM methodology is explained including
      <ns960:itemizedlist xmlns:ns960="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns961:listitem xmlns:ns961="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns962:para xmlns:ns962="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the responsibilities of the various role players within ATAM, 
        </ns962:para></ns961:listitem>
        <ns963:listitem xmlns:ns963="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns964:para xmlns:ns964="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the phases of ATAM, and
        </ns964:para></ns963:listitem>
        <ns965:listitem xmlns:ns965="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns966:para xmlns:ns966="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          the various steps of ATAM as well as the rationale behind these steps.  
        </ns966:para></ns965:listitem>
      </ns960:itemizedlist>
    </ns959:para>
  </ns957:section>
  
  <ns967:section xmlns:ns967="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns968:title xmlns:ns968="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Present the business drivers</ns968:title>
    <ns969:para xmlns:ns969="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The starting point is typically the <ns970:emphasis xmlns:ns970="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">vision and scope document</ns970:emphasis>    
      which includes
      <ns971:itemizedlist xmlns:ns971="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns972:listitem xmlns:ns972="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns973:para xmlns:ns973="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the vision the organization is trying to realize with the project,</ns973:para></ns972:listitem>
        <ns974:listitem xmlns:ns974="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns975:para xmlns:ns975="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the business objectives,</ns975:para></ns974:listitem>
        <ns976:listitem xmlns:ns976="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns977:para xmlns:ns977="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the financial context including a return on investment estimation,</ns977:para></ns976:listitem>
        <ns978:listitem xmlns:ns978="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns979:para xmlns:ns979="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core use cases (functional requirements) of the system,</ns979:para></ns978:listitem>
        <ns980:listitem xmlns:ns980="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns981:para xmlns:ns981="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the core limitations (exclusions),</ns981:para></ns980:listitem>
        <ns982:listitem xmlns:ns982="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns983:para xmlns:ns983="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any constraints placed on the project or the architecture, and</ns983:para></ns982:listitem>
        <ns984:listitem xmlns:ns984="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns985:para xmlns:ns985="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any dependencies the project may have.</ns985:para></ns984:listitem>
      </ns971:itemizedlist>
    </ns969:para>
    <ns986:para xmlns:ns986="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      In addition to this
      <ns987:itemizedlist xmlns:ns987="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns988:listitem xmlns:ns988="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns989:para xmlns:ns989="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the major stake holders,</ns989:para></ns988:listitem>
        <ns990:listitem xmlns:ns990="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns991:para xmlns:ns991="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          and the architectural drivers (<ns992:abbrev xmlns:ns992="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">i.e.</ns992:abbrev> the core quality attribute
          requirements)
        </ns991:para></ns990:listitem>
      </ns987:itemizedlist>
      need to be communicated.      
    </ns986:para>
  </ns967:section>
  
  <ns993:section xmlns:ns993="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns994:title xmlns:ns994="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Present the architecture</ns994:title>
    <ns995:para xmlns:ns995="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       The lead architect provides the essence of the architecture in a concise, structured way.
       The presentation is expected to have <ns996:quote xmlns:ns996="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns997:emphasis xmlns:ns997="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">a low signal to noise ratio</ns997:emphasis></ns996:quote>
       in the sense that it should focus on the architectural core and not stray into auxiliary details.
       The presentation should cover
       <ns998:itemizedlist xmlns:ns998="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns999:listitem xmlns:ns999="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1000:para xmlns:ns1000="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the context of the architecture which covers the environment in which the system
           will live/ is living,
         </ns1000:para></ns999:listitem>
         <ns1001:listitem xmlns:ns1001="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1002:para xmlns:ns1002="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the technical constraints (<ns1003:abbrev xmlns:ns1003="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">e.g.</ns1003:abbrev> the required deployment platforms and
           middleware technologies),
         </ns1002:para></ns1001:listitem>
         <ns1004:listitem xmlns:ns1004="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1005:para xmlns:ns1005="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
           the architectural approaches including
           <ns1006:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1006="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
             <ns1007:listitem xmlns:ns1007="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1008:para xmlns:ns1008="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">any reference architecture employed,</ns1008:para></ns1007:listitem>
             <ns1009:listitem xmlns:ns1009="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1010:para xmlns:ns1010="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the architectural patterns which were enlisted,</ns1010:para></ns1009:listitem>
             <ns1011:listitem xmlns:ns1011="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1012:para xmlns:ns1012="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">the tactics which were realized.</ns1012:para></ns1011:listitem>
           </ns1006:itemizedlist>
         </ns1005:para></ns1004:listitem>
       </ns998:itemizedlist>
       Very commonly a template for documenting architectures is conceptually followed (for example       
       the RUP template).
    </ns995:para>
  </ns993:section>
  
  <ns1013:section xmlns:ns1013="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1014:title xmlns:ns1014="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Identify architectural approaches</ns1014:title>
    <ns1015:para xmlns:ns1015="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       This step a discussion with the lead architect and the architecture team in order to
       <ns1016:emphasis xmlns:ns1016="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">verify and deepen and broaden the architectural understanding</ns1016:emphasis>.
       Usually the use further architectural patterns is identified.
    </ns1015:para>
  </ns1013:section>
  
  <ns1017:section xmlns:ns1017="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1018:title xmlns:ns1018="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Generate a quality attribute utility tree</ns1018:title>
    <ns1019:para xmlns:ns1019="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      This is perhaps the core step within ATAM. In this step one generates
      <ns1020:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1020="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1021:listitem xmlns:ns1021="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1022:para xmlns:ns1022="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a utility tree containing the quality attributes and the scenarios they affect, and
        </ns1022:para></ns1021:listitem>
        <ns1023:listitem xmlns:ns1023="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1024:para xmlns:ns1024="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          a prioritized list of scenarios extracted from the utility tree.  
        </ns1024:para></ns1023:listitem>
      </ns1020:itemizedlist>
    </ns1019:para>
    
    <ns1025:section xmlns:ns1025="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      <ns1026:title xmlns:ns1026="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Utility trees</ns1026:title>
      <ns1027:para xmlns:ns1027="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        Utility trees have 
        <ns1028:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1028="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          <ns1029:listitem xmlns:ns1029="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1030:para xmlns:ns1030="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            a quality attribute at their root,    
          </ns1030:para></ns1029:listitem>
          <ns1031:listitem xmlns:ns1031="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1032:para xmlns:ns1032="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            refined attributes in the next layer of the tree, and  
          </ns1032:para></ns1031:listitem>
          <ns1033:listitem xmlns:ns1033="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1034:para xmlns:ns1034="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
            scenarios which have a dependency on that quality attribute in the third layer.  
          </ns1034:para></ns1033:listitem>
        </ns1028:itemizedlist>
        As such they are often shown in tabular form.
      </ns1027:para>
      <ns1035:para xmlns:ns1035="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        In <ns1036:xref xmlns:ns1036="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" linkend="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.atam.methodology.elicitation.utilityTree_tbl"/>
        we show the utility of one quality attribute. Usually a table of multiple utility trees is generated.
      </ns1035:para>
      
        <ns1037:table xmlns:ns1037="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.evaluating.atam.methodology.elicitation.utilityTree_tbl">
          <ns1038:title xmlns:ns1038="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">A fragment of the utility trees for the COFLoader project</ns1038:title>
          <ns1039:tgroup xmlns:ns1039="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" cols="3">
            <ns1040:thead xmlns:ns1040="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1041:row xmlns:ns1041="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns1042:entry xmlns:ns1042="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1043:para xmlns:ns1043="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Quality attribute</ns1043:para></ns1042:entry>
                <ns1044:entry xmlns:ns1044="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1045:para xmlns:ns1045="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Attribute refinement</ns1045:para></ns1044:entry>
                <ns1046:entry xmlns:ns1046="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1047:para xmlns:ns1047="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Scenarios</ns1047:para></ns1046:entry>
              </ns1041:row>
            </ns1040:thead>
            <ns1048:tbody xmlns:ns1048="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
              <ns1049:row xmlns:ns1049="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                <ns1050:entry xmlns:ns1050="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1051:para xmlns:ns1051="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Modifiability</ns1051:para></ns1050:entry>
                <ns1052:entry xmlns:ns1052="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  <ns1053:para xmlns:ns1053="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Flexibility to modify confidence level matching.
                  </ns1053:para>
                  <ns1054:para xmlns:ns1054="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    flexibility to change data cleansing algorithm.
                  </ns1054:para>
                </ns1052:entry>
                <ns1055:entry xmlns:ns1055="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                  <ns1056:para xmlns:ns1056="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Modify field weightings.
                  </ns1056:para>
                  <ns1057:para xmlns:ns1057="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Replace rules engine for short-list selection.
                  </ns1057:para>
                  <ns1058:para xmlns:ns1058="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Modify required confidence level.
                  </ns1058:para>
                  <ns1059:para xmlns:ns1059="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
                    Modify confidence level matching algorithm.
                  </ns1059:para>
                </ns1055:entry>
              </ns1049:row>
            </ns1048:tbody>
          </ns1039:tgroup>
        </ns1037:table>
    </ns1025:section>
    
  </ns1017:section>
  
  <ns1060:section xmlns:ns1060="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
    <ns1061:title xmlns:ns1061="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Analyze architectural approaches</ns1061:title>
    <ns1062:para xmlns:ns1062="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
      The scenarios are analyzed one by one in priority order:
      <ns1063:itemizedlist xmlns:ns1063="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns1064:listitem xmlns:ns1064="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1065:para xmlns:ns1065="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The architect is asked to explain how the architecture supports each scenario.  
        </ns1065:para></ns1064:listitem>
        <ns1066:listitem xmlns:ns1066="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns1067:para xmlns:ns1067="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
          The team identifies and documents the architectural decisions with their
          risks, non-risks, sensitivity points and trade offs.  
        </ns1067:para></ns1066:listitem>
      </ns1063:itemizedlist>
    </ns1062:para>
  </ns1060:section>
  
</ns941:section>